{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011mE5WC5i5nTCdMTTjTkW4J","type":"tool_result","content":"7:  - prd-evaluator-redesign.md\n34:- Cross-cutting concerns: config resolution chain, trace ID propagation, crash recovery, evaluator isolation\n42:- Evaluator isolation: Separate workspace, no source code, Docker container for artifact\n43:- Docker: Required for evaluator but graceful degradation if missing (Journey 5)\n50:4. **Evaluator isolation** — separate workspace, `disallowedTools` enforcement, `source_access: false`\n79:2. Evaluator workspace isolation — how to enforce source-free verification\n80:3. Evaluator verdict schema — the contract between evaluator and engine\n88:- Pluggable evaluator strategies interface (Growth phase)\n97:| `workflow-engine` | Execute flow steps, manage iterations, handle `loop:` blocks, inject evaluator findings into retries | FR16-18, FR29-31 |\n99:| `evaluator` | Blind evaluator workspace setup, spawn, JSON verdict parsing | FR24-28 |\n105:### AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation\n112:  verdict/         # evaluator writes JSON verdict here\n115:Engine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n137:    evaluator.yaml\n157:### AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema\n162:interface EvaluatorVerdict {\n180:  evaluator_trace_id: string;\n185:**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n195:6. `evaluator` — depends on dispatch + state\n196:7. `circuit-breaker` — depends on evaluator verdicts\n200:- `evaluator` depends on `agent-dispatch` (for SDK spawn) and `workflow-state` (for verdict recording)\n231:**Evaluator verdict:** JSON schema enforced (AD5). No alternative formats. Every AC requires `status`, `evidence.commands_run`, `evidence.output_observed`.\n248:| Evaluator timeout | All UNKNOWN, counts as scored iteration |\n249:| Invalid evaluator JSON | Retry once, then all UNKNOWN |\n269:- Caching evaluator verdicts across iterations (each is full re-verification)\n294:│   │   ├── verify.ts                      # REWORK — becomes evaluator trigger only\n306:│   │   ├── verify-env.ts                  # REWORK — evolve into evaluator setup\n316:│   │   ├── evaluator.ts                  # Blind evaluator workspace + spawn + verdict parsing\n339:│   │   ├── verify-env.ts                 # REWORK — evolve into evaluator workspace setup\n356:│   ├── agents/                            # 9 agent YAMLs (8 BMAD + evaluator)\n365:│   │   └── evaluator.yaml\n393:- `verify.ts` — 175-line proof parser (replaced by evaluator.ts)\n394:- `verify-parser.ts` — Story AC parser (simplified into evaluator)\n395:- `verifier-session.ts` — Black-box verifier subprocess (evolved into evaluator.ts)\n402:- `verify-prompt.ts` — Black-box verifier prompt (replaced by evaluator agent YAML)\n420:| `src/lib/verify-env.ts` | Old verifier workspace logic | Evolve into evaluator workspace |\n427:| `src/commands/verify.ts` | Self-verification, proof parsing | Evaluator trigger only |\n449:- 7 core modules in `src/lib/` (workflow-parser, agent-resolver, workflow-engine, agent-dispatch, evaluator, circuit-breaker, workflow-state)\n464:| FR24-28 (Verification) | evaluator |\n494:        evaluator: setup workspace → agent-dispatch → parse verdict\n524:- Implementation sequence defined (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)\n534:- [x] Cross-cutting concerns mapped (config resolution, trace IDs, crash recovery, evaluator isolation)\n559:**Strengths:** Clean module boundaries, complete file migration plan, dependency chain breaks documented, official SDK replaces bash spawning, beads-level state simplicity, structural evaluator isolation.\n578:    title: Evaluator too lenient on API error codes\n596:3. New modules in dependency order (state → parser → resolver → dispatch → engine → evaluator → circuit-breaker)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XjpGmYRgdBb6aeHBV1bdT9","session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"7e87389b-eb1c-4ea4-b450-5ead5a836d78","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:38:39.039Z"}
