{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BakU4DTKiZh7jVjAEXGNnM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Vj6qT9XNV7qpKYAHokqiE9","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Define evaluator interfaces and types (AC: #1, #8, #9)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/evaluator.ts`\n  - [ ] Define `EvaluatorOptions` interface: `{ runId: string; storyFiles: string[]; agentDefinition: SubagentDefinition; timeoutMs?: number; traceId?: string }`\n  - [ ] Define `EvaluatorResult` interface: `{ output: string; success: boolean; durationMs: number; dockerAvailable: boolean; timedOut: boolean }`\n  - [ ] Export `runEvaluator()` function signature\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement Docker availability check (AC: #4, #5)\n  - [ ] Import `isDockerAvailable()` from `./docker/index.js`\n  - [ ] At the start of `runEvaluator()`, check Docker availability\n  - [ ] If Docker not available, return early with `EvaluatorResult` containing `dockerAvailable: false`, `success: false`, `output` set to a JSON string matching `EvaluatorVerdict` with all ACs scored UNKNOWN and reasoning explaining Docker is unavailable\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement workspace creation (AC: #2)\n  - [ ] Call `createIsolatedWorkspace({ runId, storyFiles })` from `source-isolation.ts`\n  - [ ] The workspace already creates `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/` with `story-files/` and `verdict/` subdirectories\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement evaluator agent dispatch (AC: #3)\n  - [ ] Build `DispatchOptions` from the workspace: `{ cwd: workspace.dir }`\n  - [ ] If `traceId` provided, append trace prompt via `formatTracePrompt()` to `appendSystemPrompt`\n  - [ ] Call `dispatchAgent(agentDefinition, prompt, dispatchOptions)`\n  - [ ] The prompt instructs the evaluator to read story files from `story-files/`, run verification commands, and write its verdict as JSON\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Implement timeout handling (AC: #6)\n  - [ ] Wrap `dispatchAgent()` call with `Promise.race()` against a timeout promise\n  - [ ] Default timeout: 300000ms (5 minutes)\n  - [ ] On timeout: produce `EvaluatorResult` with `timedOut: true`, `success: false`, `output` set to a JSON string with all UNKNOWN verdicts and timeout reasoning\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Implement cleanup (AC: #7)\n  - [ ] In a `finally` block after dispatch (or timeout), call `workspace.cleanup()`\n  - [ ] Ensure cleanup runs regardless of success, failure, or timeout\n\n- [ ] Task 7: Write unit tests (AC: #10)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts`\n  - [ ] Mock `dispatchAgent()` from `agent-dispatch.ts`\n  - [ ] Mock `createIsolatedWorkspace()` from `source-isolation.ts`\n  - [ ] Mock `isDockerAvailable()` from `docker/index.ts`\n  - [ ] Mock `formatTracePrompt()` from `trace-id.ts`\n  - [ ] Test: successful evaluator spawn returns output and success\n  - [ ] Test: Docker unavailable returns all-UNKNOWN result without throwing\n  - [ ] Test: timeout produces UNKNOWN result and sets `timedOut: true`\n  - [ ] Test: cleanup called on success\n  - [ ] Test: cleanup called on failure\n  - [ ] Test: cleanup called on timeout\n  - [ ] Test: workspace created with correct runId and storyFiles\n  - [ ] Test: trace ID injected when provided\n  - [ ] Test: `disallowedTools` inherited from evaluator agent definition\n  - [ ] Test: interface shapes match expected types (compile-time via TypeScript)\n  - [ ] Verify 80%+ coverage on `evaluator.ts`","new_string":"- [x] Task 1: Define evaluator interfaces and types (AC: #1, #8, #9)\n  - [x] Create `src/lib/evaluator.ts`\n  - [x] Define `EvaluatorOptions` interface: `{ runId: string; storyFiles: string[]; agentDefinition: SubagentDefinition; timeoutMs?: number; traceId?: string }`\n  - [x] Define `EvaluatorResult` interface: `{ output: string; success: boolean; durationMs: number; dockerAvailable: boo