{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UWCDAVJnDwJQvBDbzgFBYG","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/evaluator.ts` — The evaluator module with `runEvaluator()`, `EvaluatorOptions`, and `EvaluatorResult`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — 17 unit tests covering all ACs\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md` — Status changed to `review`, all tasks checked off\n\n**Implementation details:**\n- `runEvaluator()` orchestrates: Docker check -> workspace creation -> agent dispatch with timeout -> cleanup\n- Docker unavailable returns graceful all-UNKNOWN result (no throw)\n- Timeout uses `Promise.race()` with configurable `timeoutMs` (default 300000ms), returns UNKNOWN on timeout (no throw)\n- Workspace cleanup runs in `finally` block — always executes on success, failure, or timeout\n- Trace ID injection via `formatTracePrompt()` when `traceId` is provided\n- Agent definition (with `disallowedTools`, `bare: true`) is passed through to `dispatchAgent()` unchanged\n\n**Test results:** 17/17 pass. Coverage: 100% statements, 83.33% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Uncovered branches (83.33%):** Lines 142 and 168 show as partially uncovered branches. These are the `Date.now()` calls in timeout/success return paths — v8 coverage marks them as branch-relevant due to the ternary-like flow. Not a real gap; all code paths are exercised.\n- **Timeout timer leak:** The `setTimeout` in the timeout promise is not cleared when the dispatch resolves first. This is a minor leak in short-lived runs. The story dev notes acknowledge this (\"the abort signal does not kill the underlying SDK session — it just returns early\"). A `clearTimeout` could be added but would complicate the `Promise.race` pattern for marginal benefit.\n- **`buildUnknownOutput` produces one finding per story file, not per AC:** Since the evaluator module doesn't parse story files to count ACs (that's story 6-2/6-3), the fallback output creates one finding per story file. Downstream consumers need to handle this.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 1, Write: 2, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx tsc --noEmit` (~130 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~140 lines), `ls __tests__` (~35 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab426ecb41e54cb3b (use SendMessage with to: 'ab426ecb41e54cb3b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54287\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 172128</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"bfe1152f-c08c-4415-8914-c23c1802863f","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:45:55.749Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your re