{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Hsf3cdPfK7Go9jhFpuXGeq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n**Coverage:** 96.79% overall (all 159 files above 80% floor), evaluator.ts at 100/92.85/100/100 (stmt/branch/fn/line)\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed: 1 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM\n\n**HIGH: Timer leak in timeout race** — Fixed in `src/lib/evaluator.ts`. The `setTimeout` for `timeoutPromise` was never cleared on the success path. Added `clearTimeout(timeoutTimer)` in a `finally` block after `Promise.race`. This prevents the Node.js process from hanging for up to 5 minutes after a successful evaluator dispatch.\n\n**MEDIUM: Non-Error dispatch rejection untested** — Added test in `src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` for when `dispatchAgent` rejects with a string (non-Error). Confirms the error propagates and cleanup still runs.\n\n**MEDIUM: Workspace creation failure untested** — Added test confirming that when `createIsolatedWorkspace()` throws, `dispatchAgent` is never called and the error propagates correctly (the `if (workspace)` guard in `finally` handles this path).\n\n### Files Modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/evaluator.ts` — timer leak fix\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/evaluator.test.ts` — 3 new tests (20 total, up from 17)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn.md` — status `review` -> `verifying`\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: Timer leak — `setTimeout` in `Promise.race` never cleared on success path. Could keep Node.js process alive for 5 minutes after evaluator completes. **Fixed.**\n- MEDIUM: Non-Error rejection path untested. **Fixed (test added).**\n- MEDIUM: Workspace creation failure path untested. **Fixed (test added).**\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- LOW: `buildUnknownOutput` names findings `ac: index + 1` but these map to story files, not actual ACs. Misleading field naming. Acceptable per the code comment — downstream parsing (story 6-2) will handle proper AC mapping.\n- LOW: `isDockerAvailable()` is a synchronous `execFileSync` call that blocks the event loop for up to 10 seconds. Acceptable for CLI usage but would be problematic in a server context. Not this module's concern (it's in `docker/health.ts`).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch at line 160 (`if (timeoutTimer)` false branch) is unreachable in practice — `timeoutTimer` is always assigned before the try block. 92.85% branch coverage, well above floor.\n- No integration test for actual Docker interaction or real workspace I/O (all mocked). Appropriate for unit tests; integration tests are a future concern.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module boundaries are clean. No cross-concern leakage. Imports match the architecture spec exactly. The evaluator correctly delegates parsing to story 6-2 and prompt construction to story 6-3.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story passes all ACs.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0f1e0a3d9c3e130d (use SendMessage with to: 'a0f1e0a3d9c3e130d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 50852\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 154456</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"b781a748-a68f-4545-87b6-ab9a654957b5","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:49:08.213Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bm