eoutTimer` is always assigned before the try block. 92.85% branch coverage, well above floor.\n- No integration test for actual Docker interaction or real workspace I/O (all mocked). Appropriate for unit tests; integration tests are a future concern.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. Module boundaries are clean. No cross-concern leakage. Imports match the architecture spec exactly. The evaluator correctly delegates parsing to story 6-2 and prompt construction to story 6-3.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story passes all ACs.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"}],"totalDurationMs":154456,"totalTokens":50852,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":316,"cache_read_input_tokens":49568,"output_tokens":967,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":316},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
