{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AMaT8RzSmwpMr3C3vg7GD9","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"2eec495c-ce0c-4491-be3c-eef7876a322b","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:52:44.813Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none","newString":"## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — verification (2026-04-03T03:55)\n\n- **AGENTS.md stale:** `codeharness verify` flagged AGENTS.md missing `evaluator.ts` from module listing. Documentation artifact issue, not AC failure.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 3 partially relies on pre-compiled agent definition having `bare: true` and `source_access: false` — evaluator receives these, doesn't set them. By design per story dev notes.\n- **Observation:** Branch coverage 92.85% — uncovered branch at line 160 is defensive `if (timeoutTimer)` guard, hard to trigger since timer always set.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls verification/` (~133 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~60 lines), `npx vitest run` (~40 lines)\n- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest run twice (full + evaluator-only), coverage run twice — could have combined","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n\n### 5-4-run-status-commands — create-story (2026-04-03T03:15)\n\n- **Config path mismatch:** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` doesn't exist; actual config at `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n- **Sprint-status.yaml stale:** Epic 5 marked `backlog` despite 3/4 stories done.\n- **Risk:** `--resume` flag semantics ambiguous — engine already resumes by default (story 5-3). Could conflict with \"completed run early exit\" behavior.\n- **Risk:** UX spec shows richer `status` output than epic ACs cover. Story follows epic scope.\n- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 5 — purely CLI wiring, no new engine logic.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 14, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Grep: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines), `ls status/` (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 14 unique, 15 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: one redundant read of sprint-status.yaml\n\n### 5-4-run-status-commands — dev-story (2026-04-03T03:22)\n\nNo issues reported by dev agent.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 24\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 10, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 2, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), targeted tests (~28 lines), `ls` commands (~26 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 5-4-run-status-commands — code-review (2026-04-03T03:28)\n\n- **HIGH bug found & fixed:** `--resume` flag registered but never read — `options.resume` ignored, engine's `phase === 'completed'` early-exit was never bypassed.\n- **MEDIUM:** `formatElapsed` duplicated in 3 files with 3 different implementations. Not fixed — cross-cutting refactor outside story scope.\n- **MEDIUM:** 5 CLI options (`--timeout`, `--iteration-timeout`, `--calls`, `--max-story-retries`, `--reset`) parsed but never passed to EngineConfig. Pre-existing tech debt.\n- **MEDIUM:** Story File List incomplete (missing `run-helpers.ts` dependency). Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `run.ts` at 172 lines exceeds aspirational \"under 100\" guidance but within NFR9 300-line limit.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `formatElapsed` exported but only used internally in `formatters.ts`.\n- Coverage: 96.78% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 9, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff HEAD -- src/commands/run.ts` (~100 lines), `npx vitest run` (~30 lines), `npx codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — create-story (2026-04-03T03:40)\n\n- **Epic naming collision:** `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents a previous sprint's Epic 6 (Dashboard Visualization Rework), not the current Epic 6 (Blind Evaluator & Verification). Subagent navigated past it.\n- **Risk:** `EvaluatorVerdict` type already defined in `workflow-engine.ts` (story 5-2). Story 6-1's `EvaluatorResult` returns raw `output: string` — dev agent must avoid duplicating the verdict type (story 6-2 consolidates).\n- **Risk:** Timeout via `Promise.race()` does not abort the underlying SDK session. Agent may continue running after timeout. Known architectural trade-off.\n- **Observation:** Codebase already has significant evaluator infra in `workflow-engine.ts`. Story 6-1 is the \"missing middle\" — spawn lifecycle module.\n\n## Token Report — create-story\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 8, Glob: 7, Grep: 1, Write: 1, Bash: 0, Edit: 0\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — dev-story (2026-04-03T03:43)\n\n- **Uncovered branches (83.33%):** Lines 142 and 168 show partially uncovered branches. These are `Date.now()` calls in timeout/success return paths — v8 coverage marks them as branch-relevant. Not a real gap; all code paths are exercised.\n- **Timeout timer leak:** `setTimeout` in timeout promise is not cleared when dispatch resolves first. Minor leak in short-lived runs. Acknowledged trade-off.\n- **`buildUnknownOutput` produces one finding per story file, not per AC:** Evaluator module doesn't parse story files to count ACs (that's story 6-2/6-3). Downstream consumers need to handle this.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 14\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 1, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~130 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~140 lines), `ls __tests__` (~35 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — code-review (2026-04-03T03:50)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Timer leak — `setTimeout` in `Promise.race` never cleared on success path. Could keep Node.js alive 5 min after evaluator completes.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Non-Error rejection path untested (test added).\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Workspace creation failure path untested (test added).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `buildUnknownOutput` names findings `ac: index + 1` but maps to story files, not actual ACs. Misleading — downstream parsing (6-2) will handle.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `isDockerAvailable()` is synchronous `execFileSync` blocking event loop up to 10s. Acceptable for CLI.\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall, evaluator.ts 100/92.85/100/100. Branch gap at line 160 unreachable in practice.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":84,"oldLines":3,"newStart":84,"newLines":16,"lines":[" - Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)"," - Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)"," - Redundant operations: none","+","+### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — verification (2026-04-03T03:55)","+","+- **AGENTS.md stale:** `codeharness verify` flagged AGENTS.md missing `evaluator.ts` from module listing. Documentation artifact issue, not AC failure.","+- **Verification gap:** AC 3 partially relies on pre-compiled agent definition having `bare: true` and `source_access: false` — evaluator receives these, doesn't set them. By design per story dev notes.","+- **Observation:** Branch coverage 92.85% — uncovered branch at line 160 is defensive `if (timeoutTimer)` guard, hard to trigger since timer always set.","+","+## Token Report — verification","+- Total tool calls: 14","+- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1","+- Largest Bash outputs: `ls verification/` (~133 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~60 lines), `npx vitest run` (~40 lines)","+- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads","+- Redundant operations: vitest run twice (full + evaluator-only), coverage run twice — could have combined"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
