{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VXxgy4THuf8SWCfdTPnDpt","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03\n2\t\n3\t### 5-4-run-status-commands — create-story (2026-04-03T03:15)\n4\t\n5\t- **Config path mismatch:** `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` doesn't exist; actual config at `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n6\t- **Sprint-status.yaml stale:** Epic 5 marked `backlog` despite 3/4 stories done.\n7\t- **Risk:** `--resume` flag semantics ambiguous — engine already resumes by default (story 5-3). Could conflict with \"completed run early exit\" behavior.\n8\t- **Risk:** UX spec shows richer `status` output than epic ACs cover. Story follows epic scope.\n9\t- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 5 — purely CLI wiring, no new engine logic.\n10\t\n11\t## Token Report — create-story\n12\t- Total tool calls: 21\n13\t- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 14, Glob: 6, Write: 1, Grep: 1, Skill: 1\n14\t- Largest Bash outputs: `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines), `ls status/` (~6 lines)\n15\t- Files read: 14 unique, 15 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n16\t- Redundant operations: one redundant read of sprint-status.yaml\n17\t\n18\t### 5-4-run-status-commands — dev-story (2026-04-03T03:22)\n19\t\n20\tNo issues reported by dev agent.\n21\t\n22\t## Token Report — dev-story\n23\t- Total tool calls: 24\n24\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 10, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 2, Glob: 1\n25\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run` full suite (~30 lines), targeted tests (~28 lines), `ls` commands (~26 lines)\n26\t- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n27\t- Redundant operations: none\n28\t\n29\t### 5-4-run-status-commands — code-review (2026-04-03T03:28)\n30\t\n31\t- **HIGH bug found & fixed:** `--resume` flag registered but never read — `options.resume` ignored, engine's `phase === 'completed'` early-exit was never bypassed.\n32\t- **MEDIUM:** `formatElapsed` duplicated in 3 files with 3 different implementations. Not fixed — cross-cutting refactor outside story scope.\n33\t- **MEDIUM:** 5 CLI options (`--timeout`, `--iteration-timeout`, `--calls`, `--max-story-retries`, `--reset`) parsed but never passed to EngineConfig. Pre-existing tech debt.\n34\t- **MEDIUM:** Story File List incomplete (missing `run-helpers.ts` dependency). Fixed.\n35\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `run.ts` at 172 lines exceeds aspirational \"under 100\" guidance but within NFR9 300-line limit.\n36\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `formatElapsed` exported but only used internally in `formatters.ts`.\n37\t- Coverage: 96.78% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor.\n38\t\n39\t## Token Report — code-review\n40\t- Total tool calls: 22\n41\t- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 9, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n42\t- Largest Bash outputs: `git diff HEAD -- src/commands/run.ts` (~100 lines), `npx vitest run` (~30 lines), `npx codeharness coverage` (~5 lines)\n43\t- Files read: 11 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n44\t- Redundant operations: none\n45\t\n46\t### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — create-story (2026-04-03T03:40)\n47\t\n48\t- **Epic naming collision:** `epic-6-retrospective.md` documents a previous sprint's Epic 6 (Dashboard Visualization Rework), not the current Epic 6 (Blind Evaluator & Verification). Subagent navigated past it.\n49\t- **Risk:** `EvaluatorVerdict` type already defined in `workflow-engine.ts` (story 5-2). Story 6-1's `EvaluatorResult` returns raw `output: string` — dev agent must avoid duplicating the verdict type (story 6-2 consolidates).\n50\t- **Risk:** Timeout via `Promise.race()` does not abort the underlying SDK session. Agent may continue running after timeout. Known architectural trade-off.\n51\t- **Observation:** Codebase already has significant evaluator infra in `workflow-engine.ts`. Story 6-1 is the \"missing middle\" — spawn lifecycle module.\n52\t\n53\t## Token Report — create-story\n54\t- Total tool calls: 16\n55\t- By tool: Read: 8, Glob: 7, Grep: 1, Write: 1, Bash: 0, Edit: 0\n56\t- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n57\t- Redundant operations: none\n58\t\n59\t### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — dev-story (2026-04-03T03:43)\n60\t\n61\t- **Uncovered branches (83.33%):** Lines 142 and 168 show partially uncovered branches. These are `Date.now()` calls in timeout/success return paths — v8 coverage marks them as branch-relevant. Not a real gap; all code paths are exercised.\n62\t- **Timeout timer leak:** `setTimeout` in timeout promise is not cleared when dispatch resolves first. Minor leak in short-lived runs. Acknowledged trade-off.\n63\t- **`buildUnknownOutput` produces one finding per story file, not per AC:** Evaluator module doesn't parse story files to count ACs (that's story 6-2/6-3). Downstream consumers need to handle this.\n64\t\n65\t## Token Report — dev-story\n66\t- Total tool calls: 14\n67\t- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 1, Write: 2\n68\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npx tsc --noEmit` (~130 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~140 lines), `ls __tests__` (~35 lines)\n69\t- Files read: 7 unique, 7 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n70\t- Redundant operations: none\n71\t\n72\t### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — code-review (2026-04-03T03:50)\n73\t\n74\t- **HIGH fixed:** Timer leak — `setTimeout` in `Promise.race` never cleared on success path. Could keep Node.js alive 5 min after evaluator completes.\n75\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Non-Error rejection path untested (test added).\n76\t- **MEDIUM fixed:** Workspace creation failure path untested (test added).\n77\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `buildUnknownOutput` names findings `ac: index + 1` but maps to story files, not actual ACs. Misleading — downstream parsing (6-2) will handle.\n78\t- **LOW (not fixed):** `isDockerAvailable()` is synchronous `execFileSync` blocking event loop up to 10s. Acceptable for CLI.\n79\t- Coverage: 96.79% overall, evaluator.ts 100/92.85/100/100. Branch gap at line 160 unreachable in practice.\n80\t\n81\t## Token Report — code-review\n82\t- Total tool calls: 18\n83\t- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 8, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n84\t- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~40 lines), test runs (~15 lines each)\n85\t- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n86\t- Redundant operations: none\n87\t\n88\t### 6-1-evaluator-module-workspace-spawn — verification (2026-04-03T03:55)\n89\t\n90\t- **AGENTS.md stale:** `codeharness verify` flagged AGENTS.md missing `evaluator.ts` from module listing. Documentation artifact issue, not AC failure.\n91\t- **Verification gap:** AC 3 partially relies on pre-compiled agent definition having `bare: true` and `source_access: false` — evaluator receives these, doesn't set them. By design per story dev notes.\n92\t- **Observation:** Branch coverage 92.85% — uncovered branch at line 160 is defensive `if (timeoutTimer)` guard, hard to trigger since timer always set.\n93\t\n94\t## Token Report — verification\n95\t- Total tool calls: 14\n96\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1\n97\t- Largest Bash outputs: `ls verification/` (~133 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~60 lines), `npx vitest run` (~40 lines)\n98\t- Files read: 2 unique, 2 total reads\n99\t- Redundant operations: vitest run twice (full + evaluator-only), coverage run twice — could have combined\n100\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01T3wckqU5NQ1PZWusNwWmEs","session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"6d22c617-7d40-4bd8-887e-0945488d4c79","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:53:39.215Z"}
