{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YbQKSNzSmRwNzjDJMFcLXD","type":"tool_result","content":"248\t---\n249\t\n250\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n251\t\n252\t### Patterns to Repeat\n253\t\n254\t- **Review-then-verify in a dedicated session works.** Separating the review/verify from the dev phase gave a clean, focused session with no context-switching.\n255\t- **Code review on flow-control logic is essential.** Error-handling paths in orchestrators are where the worst bugs hide. Both HIGH bugs were in error-handling branches.\n256\t\n257\t### Patterns to Avoid\n258\t\n259\t- **Multiple coverage grep patterns.** Use a single grep with OR pattern or just read the coverage summary file directly.\n260\t- **Leaving AGENTS.md updates incomplete.** If updating, update all missing entries in one pass — don't leave partial debt.\n261\t\n262\t---\n263\t\n264\t## 7. Action Items\n265\t\n266\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Status |\n267\t|---|--------|----------|-------|--------|\n268\t| 1 | ~~Complete code-review and verify for story 5-1~~ | ~~HIGH~~ | ~~Next session~~ | DONE |\n269\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness verify` to work without pre-set harness state flags | MEDIUM | Backlog | Open |\n270\t| 3 | Update `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — still missing: agent-dispatch, agent-resolver, session-manager, trace-id | MEDIUM | Next session | Partial |\n271\t| 4 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work for non-ralph sessions | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n272\t| 5 | Sync `ralph/.state-snapshot.json` with `sprint-state.json` | LOW | Next session | Open |\n273\t| 6 | Fix pre-existing TS errors in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n274\t| 7 | Address deferred LOW issues from 4-3, 4-4, and 5-1 code reviews | LOW | Backlog | Open |\n275\t| 8 | Add integration test for actual YAML parsing (not mocked) in workflow-engine | LOW | Backlog | New |\n276\t\n277\t---\n278\t\n279\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 3)\n280\t\n281\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T02:45Z\n282\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T02:12 to ~2026-04-03T02:39 (approx. 27 minutes)\n283\t**Sprint progress:** 17/28 stories done (60.7%), Epics 1-4 complete, Epic 5 at 2/4\n284\t\n285\t---\n286\t\n287\t## 1. Session Summary\n288\t\n289\tThis session completed one story end-to-end within a single ralph iteration (iteration #8).\n290\t\n291\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n292\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n293\t| 5-2-flow-execution-loop-blocks | create-story, dev-story, code-review, test-provable verification | **Done** | Full lifecycle in ~27 minutes. 10/10 ACs passed. Commit `1219d18`. |\n294\t\n295\t**Key deliverables:**\n296\t- `executeLoopBlock()` — loop block execution with termination on pass/maxIterations/circuit-breaker\n297\t- `parseVerdict()` — EvaluatorVerdict JSON parsing from dispatch output\n298\t- `buildRetryPrompt()` — finding injection into retry prompts\n299\t- `getFailedItems()` — failed-story-only retry filtering\n300\t- 27+ new tests, 3992 total tests passing, 96.37% statement coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n301\t\n302\t---\n303\t\n304\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n305\t\n306\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed)\n307\t\n308\t| Severity | Issue | Impact |\n309\t|----------|-------|--------|\n310\t| HIGH | **Stale verdict bug** — verdict from a previous loop iteration could persist and cause premature loop termination on the next pass | Correctness: loop would exit early based on old evaluation results |\n311\t| HIGH | **80-line code duplication** — loop block dispatch logic duplicated the sequential step dispatch logic nearly verbatim | Maintainability: two copies of error handling, checkpoint logic, state updates that would diverge over time |\n312\t| HIGH | **Uncovered branches in duplicate code** — the duplicated code paths had no dedicated test coverage | Quality: bugs in the duplicate path would go undetected |\n313\t\n314\tAll three HIGH issues were fixed during code review before verification.\n315\t\n316\t### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n317\t\n318\tPer the parent session summary, 3 MEDIUM issues were also addressed during code review, likely related to coverage gaps and edge case handling.\n319\t\n320\t### Infrastructure Issues\n321\t\n322\t- **Session issues log stale** — `.session-issues.md` still contains only placeholder entries from 2026-03-18. The subagents this session did not write to it. The session issues log mechanism is non-functional for ralph-driven sessions.\n323\t- **`codeharness stats` still broken** — `stats --save` and `stats --json` both fail with \"No session-logs/ directory found.\" Cost analysis remains manual.\n324\t- **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` divergence** — Shows `sprint.done: 12` but sprint-status.yaml shows 17 done. The state snapshot does not update Epic 5 stories as done (shows `storiesDone: 0` for Epic 5 despite 2 stories completed).\n325\t\n326\t---\n327\t\n328\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n329\t\n330\t### Session-Level Metrics\n331\t\n332\t| Metric | Value |\n333\t|--------|-------|\n334\t| Ralph iteration | #8 (of the current ralph run) |\n335\t| Log file size | 2.42 MB (`claude_output_2026-04-03_02-12-22.log`) |\n336\t| Session wall time | ~27 minutes |\n337\t| Phases completed | 4 (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification) |\n338\t\n339\t### Estimated Token Usage\n340\t\n341\tBased on log file size (2.42 MB of stream-json output) and prior session correlations:\n342\t- Estimated API calls: ~15-25 (4 phases, each 4-7 tool calls)\n343\t- Estimated session cost: **~$4-5** (single story, full lifecycle)\n344\t- Cost per phase (estimated): create-story ~$0.50, dev-story ~$1.50, code-review ~$1.50, verification ~$0.75\n345\t\n346\t### Subagent Analysis (from parent session live log)\n347\t\n348\tThe parent orchestrator launched this iteration at 02:12:22 and it completed at 02:39. The background retro agent consumed 23+ tool calls reading logs and state files — indicating the retro itself is a significant cost center.\n349\t\n350\tFrom the parent's output summary:\n351\t- 10/10 ACs verified on first attempt\n352\t- 3992/3992 tests passing\n353\t- 96.37% coverage on workflow-engine.ts\n354\t- 3 HIGH + 3 MEDIUM bugs found and fixed\n355\t\n356\t### Cumulative Cost Tracking\n357\t\n358\t| Session | Stories Completed | Estimated Cost | Cost/Story |\n359\t|---------|-------------------|---------------|------------|\n360\t| Prior sessions (Epics 1-2) | 7 | $37.08 | $4.45 |\n361\t| Session 1 (2026-04-03, early) | 2.5 | ~$12 | ~$4.80 |\n362\t| Session 2 (2026-04-03, late) | 0.5 (review+verify) | ~$3.50 | ~$7.00* |\n363\t| **Session 3 (this)** | **1** | **~$4.50** | **~$4.50** |\n364\t| **Cumulative** | **11** | **~$57** | **~$5.18** |\n365\t\n366\t*Session 2 cost/story is misleading — it was the tail end of a story built in Session 1.\n367\t\n368\t---\n369\t\n370\t## 4. What Went Well\n371\t\n372\t1. **Full lifecycle in one iteration.** Story 5-2 went from backlog to verified in a single 27-minute ralph iteration. This is the fastest full-lifecycle story completion yet.\n373\t2. **All phases passed on first attempt.** No retries, no stuck phases, no timeouts. The pipeline ran clean.\n374\t3. **Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs.** The stale verdict bug would have caused incorrect loop behavior in production. The 80-line duplication was a significant maintenance risk. Code review continues to earn its keep.\n375\t4. **High coverage.** 96.37% statement, 88.75% branch, 100% function coverage on the primary module. 27 new tests added.\n376\t5. **Budget adherence.** Completed in 27 minutes within a 30-minute timeout window. No timeout, no waste.\n377\t6. **Sprint velocity.** With 17/28 stories done (60.7%), the project is past the halfway mark. Epic 5 is at 50% (2/4).\n378\t\n379\t---\n380\t\n381\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n382\t\n383\t1. **Session issues log is non-functional.** `.session-issues.md` was not updated by any subagent this session. It still contains placeholder data from 2026-03-18. Without subagent self-reporting, cost analysis and issue tracking rely entirely on log file archaeology.\n384\t2. **`ralph/.state-snapshot.json` is increasingly stale.** Shows `sprint.done: 12` vs actual 17. Epic 5 `storiesDone: 0` despite 2 stories completed. The snapshot update mechanism is broken or not running after story completion.\n385\t3. **`codeharness stats` still broken.** Third consecutive session where cost reporting is unavailable. No `session-logs/` directory exists for ralph-driven sessions.\n386\t4. **Sprint-status.yaml was overwritten.** The parent orchestrator rewrote the entire sprint-status.yaml file (see live log line 4229). While the content was correct, the approach is fragile — it replaced a stale \"Epic Infinity\" placeholder that existed from an earlier bug, which means the file was corrupted at some point.\n387\t\n388\t---\n389\t\n390\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n391\t\n392\t### Patterns to Repeat\n393\t\n394\t- **Single-story-per-iteration pipeline.** The create → dev → review → verify pipeline completing in one iteration is the ideal execution pattern. No context switching, no state management between iterations.\n395\t- **Code review on loop/retry logic.** The stale verdict bug is exactly the kind of state-mutation bug that only appears under iteration. Always review loops and retry logic adversarially.\n396\t- **Building on prior story foundations.** Story 5-2 built directly on 5-1's sequential execution, reusing the same dispatch/checkpoint/error-handling patterns. Incremental stories within an epic pay off in velocity.\n397\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01T3wckqU5NQ1PZWusNwWmEs","session_id":"e9c90575-92e6-47e7-805a-c4ec47a0ac4f","uuid":"12ad370c-4714-45b6-beaa-87f5b4878ce3","timestamp":"2026-04-02T23:53:57.509Z"}
